📈 BVMT Historical Indices Scraper
This repository contains a Python script (bvmt_scraper.py) designed to automate the downloading, extraction, parsing, cleaning, and consolidation of historical index data from the Bourse de Tunis (BVMT) official website. The script processes data from the year 2008 to 2024 and produces a single consolidated CSV file suitable for analysis.

🔥 Features
✅ Downloads yearly index data archives (.rar, .zip) from BVMT.

✅ Extracts and processes various file formats (CSV, TXT, fixed-width, mixed-format).

✅ Cleans numeric columns with European formatting and standardizes data.

✅ Handles multiple date formats and corrects common issues.

✅ Generates consolidated CSV file indices.csv for all years combined.

✅ Provides detailed logs and an execution summary.

📂 Output
Cleaned per-year CSVs: saved in the csv/ directory.

Final consolidated CSV: saved at ../data/input/indices.csv.

Log file: bvmt_scraper.log.

🚀 Requirements
Python 3.7+

The following Python packages:

bash
Copy
Edit
pandas
requests
rarfile
lxml  # For parsing HTML (used in alternate sources)
Install them via:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install pandas requests rarfile lxml
For RAR file extraction, make sure the unrar utility is installed on your system:

On Ubuntu/Debian:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo apt-get install unrar
On Windows, install WinRAR and ensure it's in your system PATH.

🛠️ Usage
Clone the repository or place the script in your desired folder.

Run the script:

bash
Copy
Edit
python bvmt_scraper.py
Wait for the process to complete.
The script will:

Download files from 2008 to 2024.

Extract and clean the data.

Save the consolidated CSV at ../data/input/indices.csv.

Show a summary at the end.

